msDesc.head: Gregory the Great, Homilies on Ezekiel

p.note: Paste-down on is covered by an ex libris measuring 250 x 165 mm. Text: Ex Bibliotheca, Illustrissimi Principis, Domini Domini Petri Vok, Ursini, Domino Domus à Rosenberg, Ultimi & Senioris, & è Primatibus Bohemorum celsissimi, et antiquis: ANNO CHRISTI M.DC.IX. Woman on the left holding a plaque reading VERBVM DOMINI MANET IN ETERNVM. At the bottom a skull and bones in relief with inscription IN SILENTIO ET SPE. Below this the signature of the artist: S.C.M. Sculptor AEg. Sadeler Fecit.

collation.formula: 1-3(8), 4(10, lacks one leaf after f. 33v), 5-6(8), 7(10, lacks one leaf between f. 51 and 52 and one leaf between f. 54 and 55), 8-9(8), 10(8, lacks one leaf between f. 77 and 78), 11-15(8), 16(12, lacks one leaf between f. 125 and 126, and one leaf after f. 130), 17-19(8), 20(8, lacks three leaves after f. 159)

binding.p: Half-bound with white leather on spine; brown wooden boards; metal clasps remaining on . Two endbands and four double bands. Label on second panel on spine: No 36 Homiliae latinae. Mi Isidori libri sententiarum. Liber Amalarii de rebus et ordine Romanae Ecclesiae. , label on fourth panel: 36.; label on bottom panel: e. 30. 4. 11.

p.note: Contemporary corrections, nota-signs and manicules in the margins throughout the manuscript.
